quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  54,7,"with down-cast eyes they shall go forth from their graves, as though they were scattered locusts.",footnotes:181755:1,footnotes:181756:2
  54,8,"They shall be hurrying forth towards the caller, and the unbelievers (who had once denied this Day), will say: “This is a woeful Day.”"
  54,9,"Before them Noah's people also gave the lie (to his Message). They rejected Our servant as a liar, saying: “He is a madman”; and he was rebuffed.",footnotes:181757:1,footnotes:181758:2
  54,10,"Then he called upon His Lord: “Verily I am vanquished; so come You to my aid.”"